MESSAGE.value: Finished for the day
Improving frontend with better instructions, adding shortcut keys, etc.
Added hotkeys, which actually seem to not suck. Now need to make instructions dismissable, etc.
Transition to Jetty 9 seems to fix issues with dropping websocket connections. Hope that's just the end of it.
Made such pretty.
Changed to a simplified NER setup.
Added a bunch of logic to try to make sure we don't accidentally stiff real workers.
Reasonable response to multiple simultaneous requests from the same client.
Added a budget mechanism to cap spending by the algorithm. Seems thread-safe, but probably needs at least a once-over by someone smart.
Added budget mechanism for retainer.
Added a waiting mechanism. Now just need to make sure that questions can time out, and then I think we're in gravy.
Fixed bugs with interpretability in strict mode on Firefox and mobile browsers.
Adding tuning curve analysis, with some expectedly poor results for bag of words models.
Adding a craigslist and sentiment use case. Still debugging sentiment, it seems to throw NPEs in odd places.
Fixed edge case where loss function was calculated over graph which already had stored MAP estimate as obseved values, so was returning an empty set for marginals.
Adding word embedding features to both craigslist and sentiment models. Need to double check that sentiment makes sense, then launch against real humans.
Refactored the gameplaying section and wrote some intro docs.
Further enriching the readme.
Notes on budget
Added mechanism for sending tutorials to the prospective workers. Need to write front-end. Should probably pay down some technical debt before writing anything more elaborate.
Front-end is configured to allow pushing tutorials to the humans before they get started, so hopefully it will be possible to train them to reasonable performance.
Tweaking front-end to improve styling and fix minor behavior glitches.
More fine-tuning of interface, removing the showing of tutorial if no tutorial is specified.
Started working on Expected-Utility gameplayer.
Changed the testWithRealHumans to only wait for 1 person, which makes demos a lot easier.
